   2. Review the program's control flow and error handling mechanisms to ensure
   correct behavior.
   3. Address any inconsistencies or defects found in the code.
   4. Update the implementation of `main()` and `exit_shell()` to handle errors
   correctly.
   
   This thorough fix involves a more in-depth analysis of the program's code and
   control flow to identify and address the root cause of the issue.
